1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:32,000
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:00:39,175 --> 00:00:40,645
(All characters, places,
and organizations are fictional.)

3
00:00:40,645 --> 00:00:42,075
(Children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:43,385 --> 00:00:45,385
(Episode 14)

5
00:00:45,555 --> 00:00:48,785
I stopped by to say hello,
but the lights were off.

6
00:00:48,985 --> 00:00:50,825
So I figured you hadn't
come back from Germany yet.

7
00:00:52,395 --> 00:00:53,855
I got back a few days ago.

8
00:00:54,595 --> 00:00:56,665
The elderly woman you're looking after,
is she able to get around?

9
00:00:56,895 --> 00:01:00,165
Yes. She just has some minor heart
and blood pressure issues,

10
00:01:00,295 --> 00:01:02,335
but she's very good about
taking all her medication.

11
00:01:02,805 --> 00:01:04,735
I'm really just there to keep her company,

12
00:01:05,365 --> 00:01:08,805
so I feel a little guilty
getting paid for such an easy job.

13
00:01:08,945 --> 00:01:12,145
I'm sure her family is relieved, though.

14
00:01:12,545 --> 00:01:14,145
Knowing she's being cared for...

15
00:01:14,145 --> 00:01:16,245
by a kind person like you
and not a total stranger.

16
00:01:16,985 --> 00:01:20,755
I'd say I'm more lukewarm than kind.

17
00:01:22,285 --> 00:01:26,795
Honestly, it feels more like
she's taking care of me.

18
00:01:27,125 --> 00:01:30,225
She tells me great stories,
and she's someone I can really lean on.

19
00:01:30,895 --> 00:01:32,025
When I go back this time,

20
00:01:33,435 --> 00:01:35,705
I might be gone for a while.

21
00:01:36,665 --> 00:01:39,635
I want to stay by his side
until his treatment is finished.

22
00:01:40,635 --> 00:01:42,545
He used to have a girlfriend,
but she left him.

23
00:01:45,475 --> 00:01:46,875
Since you're nearby,

24
00:01:46,875 --> 00:01:49,515
could you check on this place
once in a while?

25
00:01:49,815 --> 00:01:51,515
Bring in the mail and things like that.

26
00:01:51,945 --> 00:01:53,685
Of course. When are you leaving?

27
00:01:53,815 --> 00:01:57,325
I have some things to finish up.
I'll leave this week, once I get a ticket.

28
00:01:59,095 --> 00:02:02,095
You get regular checkups, don't you?

29
00:02:02,995 --> 00:02:06,335
I got one when I came back last year.
They said nothing was wrong.

30
00:02:06,565 --> 00:02:07,965
You should get one every year.

31
00:02:08,635 --> 00:02:10,005
Reporter Geum, how are your parents?

32
00:02:13,135 --> 00:02:14,175
Yes, Grandma.

33
00:02:14,875 --> 00:02:17,675
I'll be there in a minute. I'm close by.
Okay.

34
00:02:20,045 --> 00:02:22,175
She said she can't find
the pain relief patches.

35
00:02:23,385 --> 00:02:25,545
I'll let you go then.

36
00:02:28,155 --> 00:02:29,155
Right.

37
00:02:29,525 --> 00:02:32,655
- No, don't worry about it.
- I'll just leave it there for you.

38
00:02:44,435 --> 00:02:47,305
- I'm glad I got to see you, though.
- Me too.

39
00:02:47,875 --> 00:02:50,705
I sometimes worry
since it's a detached house.

40
00:02:51,045 --> 00:02:52,675
By the way, my number changed.

41
00:02:55,415 --> 00:02:56,785
I'll text it to you.

42
00:02:57,315 --> 00:03:00,685
- Okay.
- I know it's tough with a sick person,

43
00:03:01,815 --> 00:03:03,155
but have a safe trip.

44
00:03:03,425 --> 00:03:07,295
- Thanks. I'll walk you out.
- It's only a ten-minute walk.

45
00:03:08,755 --> 00:03:10,825
- Still, she's waiting...
- Hey, your phone is ringing.

46
00:03:14,195 --> 00:03:15,265
Okay, just text me then.

47
00:03:15,805 --> 00:03:16,805
Okay, I will.

48
00:03:41,625 --> 00:03:42,995
(Kim Young Jun:
The door passcode is 8-8-3-2.)

49
00:04:03,015 --> 00:04:05,885
The car will just go to waste here,
so feel free to use it.

50
00:04:06,385 --> 00:04:08,215
The insurance covers any driver.

51
00:04:11,155 --> 00:04:14,155
The freezer is full of
ingredients people have sent me.

52
00:04:14,895 --> 00:04:17,125
Please help yourself to anything you need.
I'd really appreciate it.

53
00:04:19,595 --> 00:04:21,835
I'm sure you need some time
to yourself as well.

54
00:04:22,405 --> 00:04:24,365
Come by whenever
and make yourself at home.

55
00:04:24,865 --> 00:04:27,405
Listen to some music or read a book.

56
00:04:33,045 --> 00:04:36,345
I suddenly got a craving for the sea bream
and seaweed soup my mom used to make,

57
00:04:36,915 --> 00:04:39,315
so I tried making it from memory
for the first time.

58
00:04:39,755 --> 00:04:41,615
I think it tastes pretty similar,
to me at least.

59
00:04:42,055 --> 00:04:43,385
But I made way too much.

60
00:04:43,385 --> 00:04:46,295
I put a container in the fridge,
so give it a try.

61
00:04:52,435 --> 00:04:53,495
You can always try again.

62
00:04:57,135 --> 00:05:00,135
I guess this is her punishment
for throwing away such a blessing.

63
00:05:01,005 --> 00:05:03,405
Now she came in
and snatched up my precious brother...

64
00:05:07,215 --> 00:05:09,885
Yong Joong must be devastated
when even I feel this bad.

65
00:05:11,945 --> 00:05:13,255
And Reporter Geum...

66
00:05:15,825 --> 00:05:18,655
It's like she vanished into thin air
or was swallowed by the earth.

67
00:05:20,225 --> 00:05:21,425
I miss her so much.

68
00:05:23,825 --> 00:05:25,065
What if she's despairing
over her situation...

69
00:05:26,865 --> 00:05:28,865
No, I shouldn't even think about that.

70
00:06:14,845 --> 00:06:16,445
A part of me thinks it's for the best.

71
00:06:20,515 --> 00:06:21,685
I'd rather have a son anyway.

72
00:06:22,415 --> 00:06:24,085
We'll have a son next time.

73
00:06:24,155 --> 00:06:25,625
Just focus on recovering for now.

74
00:06:26,155 --> 00:06:27,595
And no swimming for a while.

75
00:06:28,895 --> 00:06:29,895
What did your brother say?

76
00:06:30,195 --> 00:06:31,195
What do you think?

77
00:06:31,895 --> 00:06:32,965
What did he say?

78
00:06:34,095 --> 00:06:35,365
He said we can always try again.

79
00:06:36,205 --> 00:06:37,835
And he wasn't worried about me?

80
00:06:38,305 --> 00:06:39,475
It was a quick call.

81
00:06:40,005 --> 00:06:42,945
- Of course he was.
- I bet he was secretly thrilled.

82
00:06:43,275 --> 00:06:45,875
He was more excited than anyone
about having a niece or nephew.

83
00:06:46,415 --> 00:06:49,175
I'm telling you, his feelings toward me
changed the minute we got married.

84
00:06:49,585 --> 00:06:50,745
Don't jump to conclusions.

85
00:06:51,345 --> 00:06:52,685
You're just clueless about these things.

86
00:07:00,495 --> 00:07:01,495
Do we have any soy milk?

87
00:07:02,155 --> 00:07:03,925
- I'll go get some.
- No, don't.

88
00:07:04,725 --> 00:07:05,825
I don't want to be alone.

89
00:07:28,655 --> 00:07:31,125
Have you heard from Ba Ra?

90
00:07:34,425 --> 00:07:35,425
Are you worried about her?

91
00:07:36,665 --> 00:07:37,825
She's on my mind.

92
00:07:38,095 --> 00:07:39,795
That's why she disappeared.

93
00:07:39,795 --> 00:07:41,965
She wants everyone
to miss her and worry about her.

94
00:07:42,395 --> 00:07:44,365
I bet she's doing just fine somewhere.

95
00:07:45,065 --> 00:07:46,075
Doing what?

96
00:07:46,435 --> 00:07:49,035
Maybe a part-time job in the south,
at a cram school or something.

97
00:07:49,745 --> 00:07:50,975
That'd be a relief if it's true.

98
00:07:52,105 --> 00:07:53,475
Don't make me worried.

99
00:07:54,345 --> 00:07:56,185
We won't be able to have a baby
if I'm stressed out.

100
00:08:08,855 --> 00:08:10,625
(Pregnancy Test)

101
00:08:17,805 --> 00:08:19,935
Come over for brunch tomorrow.
Yong Joong will be here.

102
00:08:20,305 --> 00:08:22,605
- You know it's your birthday, right?
- It's my birthday?

103
00:08:23,075 --> 00:08:25,375
Gosh, you don't even
know your own birthday?

104
00:08:25,645 --> 00:08:28,775
I'm fine.
You're busy, so don't trouble yourself.

105
00:08:28,775 --> 00:08:29,985
But I want to.

106
00:08:30,445 --> 00:08:31,785
Is it so hard to have one meal together?

107
00:08:32,545 --> 00:08:35,385
- Besides, it's been so long since we met.
- Then let's eat out.

108
00:08:35,755 --> 00:08:37,425
The birthday boy is supposed to treat,
you know.

109
00:08:37,485 --> 00:08:40,295
I'm so sick of eating out.

110
00:09:17,225 --> 00:09:18,265
(Call Log)

111
00:09:18,265 --> 00:09:19,935
(Chairman Park, Reporter Yoon Oh Cheol...)

112
00:09:24,865 --> 00:09:26,375
(Unread messages)

113
00:09:26,435 --> 00:09:27,775
(Team Leader Yoon Young Chan...)

114
00:09:27,835 --> 00:09:29,205
(Development Team's Manager Kim...)

115
00:09:31,905 --> 00:09:33,915
(Park Il Joon,
Operations Team's Manager Choi...)

116
00:09:53,665 --> 00:09:55,165
It's opened up perfectly.

117
00:10:03,375 --> 00:10:04,745
First time eating here, right?

118
00:10:05,345 --> 00:10:07,045
- Yes.
- Happy birthday.

119
00:10:07,445 --> 00:10:08,845
To our personal physician.

120
00:10:16,755 --> 00:10:17,825
I feel like I'm always taking from you.

121
00:10:17,885 --> 00:10:21,825
What are you talking about?
I loved the abalone you sent last time.

122
00:10:21,895 --> 00:10:23,195
That was just something I got
and passed along.

123
00:10:23,265 --> 00:10:25,525
Tossed or whatever, it was delicious.

124
00:10:25,595 --> 00:10:27,395
You could have passed it to someone else.

125
00:10:28,035 --> 00:10:29,265
Eat before your soup gets cold.

126
00:10:32,875 --> 00:10:34,505
I wonder if the seasoning
is to your liking.

127
00:10:34,975 --> 00:10:36,945
It might be a bit bland for you,
Director Shin.

128
00:10:37,805 --> 00:10:39,275
A doctor should practice what he preaches.

129
00:10:40,345 --> 00:10:42,175
- What's this?
- Cazuela.

130
00:10:42,375 --> 00:10:44,015
I enjoyed it in Madrid.

131
00:10:44,915 --> 00:10:46,315
Scoop some out and put it on the bread.

132
00:10:47,855 --> 00:10:49,455
You always make way too much.

133
00:10:49,725 --> 00:10:50,785
Don't worry.

134
00:10:51,355 --> 00:10:53,525
I just freeze the leftovers
and eat them all myself.

135
00:10:54,525 --> 00:10:56,795
A birthday calls
for a proper feast like this.

136
00:10:58,965 --> 00:11:01,865
I'm starting to wonder if
Reporter Geum joined a monastery.

137
00:11:04,705 --> 00:11:06,475
How else could she have vanished
without a trace?

138
00:11:09,005 --> 00:11:10,005
I doubt it.

139
00:11:10,245 --> 00:11:13,515
It's been over six months with no word,
not just a month or two.

140
00:11:14,945 --> 00:11:17,245
Should I check with
the Jogye Order office at Jogyesa?

141
00:11:22,255 --> 00:11:24,185
Manager Yoon. What is it?

142
00:11:24,485 --> 00:11:28,795
Park Sun Woo said she just saw
Reporter Geum at a rest stop.

143
00:11:29,455 --> 00:11:31,295
- Reporter Geum Ba Ra?
- Yes.

144
00:11:32,065 --> 00:11:33,965
- Which rest stop?
- Let me ask her.

145
00:11:34,035 --> 00:11:35,035
No, wait. Hold on.

146
00:11:35,435 --> 00:11:37,335
Who was with her?
And she's sure it was Reporter Geum?

147
00:11:37,405 --> 00:11:39,435
Park Sun Woo wouldn't be mistaken.

148
00:11:39,875 --> 00:11:41,205
She was with an elderly woman.

149
00:11:43,375 --> 00:11:44,375
An elderly woman?

150
00:11:45,175 --> 00:11:46,945
- But...
- But what?

151
00:11:47,445 --> 00:11:49,015
She said she looked different.

152
00:11:50,215 --> 00:11:51,445
Looked different?

153
00:11:52,045 --> 00:11:53,455
Her belly was showing.

154
00:11:55,285 --> 00:11:56,785
- You mean she's pregnant?
- Yes.

155
00:11:59,185 --> 00:12:00,255
How far along did she look?

156
00:12:02,555 --> 00:12:04,225
No. She must be mistaken.

157
00:12:05,295 --> 00:12:06,735
She says she's positive.

158
00:12:07,335 --> 00:12:08,735
I didn't believe it at first, either.

159
00:12:09,435 --> 00:12:10,505
And she didn't say anything to her?

160
00:12:10,635 --> 00:12:12,765
She saw her helping the elderly woman
into a car,

161
00:12:13,035 --> 00:12:15,835
but Park Sun Woo's husband had to rush
to the restroom, so she couldn't get out.

162
00:12:16,205 --> 00:12:17,475
Right as they were pulling
into the rest stop...

163
00:12:17,545 --> 00:12:18,775
Ask them which rest stop it was.

164
00:12:18,775 --> 00:12:20,315
Ask how far along she looked...

165
00:12:20,815 --> 00:12:22,945
- and if Reporter Geum saw Sun Woo.
- Okay.

166
00:12:28,815 --> 00:12:30,185
What is going on?

167
00:12:45,265 --> 00:12:46,275
You haven't heard?

168
00:12:52,605 --> 00:12:54,145
(Manager Yoon)

169
00:12:55,675 --> 00:12:58,345
(Manager Yoon)

170
00:12:59,115 --> 00:13:01,615
- Yes.
- It was the Meeting Plaza.

171
00:13:02,015 --> 00:13:05,225
She looked six or seven months along.
Maybe five?

172
00:13:05,225 --> 00:13:06,555
Did she say she looked happy?

173
00:13:06,955 --> 00:13:09,865
- Did she seem to be doing well?
- She said she seemed fine.

174
00:13:10,195 --> 00:13:12,195
What about inside the car?
Who else was there?

175
00:13:12,325 --> 00:13:13,995
She couldn't see that.

176
00:13:14,065 --> 00:13:16,635
But she said it was definitely Geum Ba Ra.

177
00:13:16,935 --> 00:13:19,465
She has such a unique face.
There's no way they were mistaken.

178
00:13:19,535 --> 00:13:22,235
But if her husband was in a rush,
she could've grabbed her phone and left.

179
00:13:22,305 --> 00:13:23,575
Park Sun Woo was driving.

180
00:13:23,645 --> 00:13:25,405
Then she could've told him to get out
and run for it.

181
00:13:25,475 --> 00:13:27,115
It's a busy rest stop.
Cars are always coming in.

182
00:13:28,645 --> 00:13:31,985
- All right.
- Maybe she's with a regular guy?

183
00:13:32,145 --> 00:13:33,785
- You can go now.
- Okay.

184
00:13:38,655 --> 00:13:40,455
Could Manager Yoon be right?

185
00:13:40,595 --> 00:13:41,955
If she's six or seven months along,

186
00:13:42,555 --> 00:13:44,765
that means she got pregnant
after she disappeared.

187
00:13:46,935 --> 00:13:49,935
It's crazy, but she's sure she saw her,
so we have no choice but to believe her.

188
00:13:50,505 --> 00:13:51,535
If she were at Meeting Plaza,

189
00:13:51,535 --> 00:13:53,535
does she live
in Seoul or just passing through?

190
00:13:53,775 --> 00:13:54,905
Is she on a trip?

191
00:14:06,115 --> 00:14:09,385
You have a beautiful baby.
How many months is she?

192
00:14:09,685 --> 00:14:10,755
She's nine months.

193
00:14:11,885 --> 00:14:13,625
Do you live here at the painter's house?

194
00:14:14,025 --> 00:14:17,995
No. He's abroad at the moment,
so I just check on the house now and then.

195
00:14:19,525 --> 00:14:22,865
When are you due?
Are you about six months along?

196
00:14:23,465 --> 00:14:24,965
The 12th of next month.

197
00:14:24,965 --> 00:14:26,975
Goodness. Is it your first baby?

198
00:14:27,335 --> 00:14:30,145
- Yes.
- I was huge when I was pregnant.

199
00:14:30,375 --> 00:14:33,415
My mother-in-law wants another already.

200
00:14:33,415 --> 00:14:34,515
Gosh, already?

201
00:14:35,515 --> 00:14:37,285
Her health isn't great.

202
00:17:31,425 --> 00:17:33,295
Hyun Ran Hee visited today.

203
00:17:34,525 --> 00:17:37,265
Momo's mom, CEO Hyun?

204
00:17:40,495 --> 00:17:42,635
Even though my face has changed,

205
00:17:42,965 --> 00:17:44,935
how could she not even remember my voice?

206
00:17:45,935 --> 00:17:47,275
Even if she'd forgotten me,

207
00:17:47,475 --> 00:17:50,005
how could she completely forget
the child she gave birth to...

208
00:17:50,445 --> 00:17:52,305
and go on living as if nothing happened?

209
00:17:53,045 --> 00:17:54,775
I just can't understand it.

210
00:17:55,645 --> 00:17:56,645
She's a mother, after all.

211
00:18:03,285 --> 00:18:05,325
She asked about the child
so mechanically...

212
00:18:05,655 --> 00:18:07,255
and then left without a word.

213
00:18:08,195 --> 00:18:10,565
As for me,
any old feelings I had for Hyun Ran Hee

214
00:18:10,895 --> 00:18:12,595
are completely gone.

215
00:18:12,595 --> 00:18:15,695
All I want is to find our daughter.

216
00:18:17,805 --> 00:18:19,565
"Our daughter?"

217
00:18:27,415 --> 00:18:28,715
Hyun Ran Hee is dead.

218
00:18:29,345 --> 00:18:31,585
She took her own life.

219
00:18:32,545 --> 00:18:34,315
If only I had answered her call
that night,

220
00:18:34,615 --> 00:18:36,625
she might not have made that decision.

221
00:18:37,285 --> 00:18:38,855
She might still be alive.

222
00:18:41,555 --> 00:18:43,265
I'm worried about Momo.

223
00:18:43,265 --> 00:18:44,565
How will she cope?

224
00:18:45,465 --> 00:18:46,565
And how will she go on living?

225
00:18:48,865 --> 00:18:49,865
Momo?

226
00:18:54,005 --> 00:18:58,545
Momo left, asking me to let her know
if I found her sister.

227
00:18:59,375 --> 00:19:01,275
I'm the one who's desperate to find her.

228
00:19:02,875 --> 00:19:05,845
My baby's eyes, nose, and mouth.

229
00:19:06,315 --> 00:19:07,855
I can still see them so clearly,

230
00:19:08,585 --> 00:19:10,555
but why didn't I think to take a picture?

231
00:19:11,025 --> 00:19:12,985
Even in all the chaos,
I should have taken one.

232
00:19:13,825 --> 00:19:15,395
I don't deserve to be a father.

233
00:19:16,225 --> 00:19:17,625
How will I ever live with this guilt?

234
00:19:18,425 --> 00:19:19,465
I'm so sad,

235
00:19:20,265 --> 00:19:21,295
and it hurts so much.

236
00:19:28,275 --> 00:19:29,505
It can't be true.

237
00:19:32,505 --> 00:19:34,715
When I heard from Mr. Park
that he'd found Kim Jin Ju,

238
00:19:34,775 --> 00:19:38,845
the whole world felt like paradise.

239
00:19:39,615 --> 00:19:40,615
But it wasn't her.

240
00:19:41,415 --> 00:19:43,585
Where in the world could my daughter,
Kim Jin Ju, be?

241
00:19:44,585 --> 00:19:45,955
Please, just be alive.

242
00:19:46,795 --> 00:19:48,295
I pray the sky is watching over her...

243
00:19:48,955 --> 00:19:50,125
again today.

244
00:19:50,465 --> 00:19:52,765
Congratulations. This is such a surprise.

245
00:19:53,195 --> 00:19:56,335
It feels like a dream.
I really hope he's my dad.

246
00:20:00,235 --> 00:20:02,475
Are the results not a match?

247
00:20:03,445 --> 00:20:04,605
Not a match.

248
00:21:48,975 --> 00:21:50,315
I'm just giving it a shot.

249
00:21:51,245 --> 00:21:52,515
So I won't have any what-ifs.

250
00:21:53,515 --> 00:21:54,555
And no regrets.

251
00:22:34,425 --> 00:22:35,555
I have something to say.

252
00:22:35,925 --> 00:22:37,595
My wife isn't home yet.

253
00:22:39,965 --> 00:22:41,435
You know I got fired, right?

254
00:22:42,365 --> 00:22:44,235
I was fired.
I hadn't even been here one month.

255
00:22:46,235 --> 00:22:47,575
This is ridiculous.

256
00:22:47,975 --> 00:22:48,975
Why?

257
00:22:56,045 --> 00:22:58,045
(Hospital Director, Shin Ju Shin)

258
00:23:38,185 --> 00:23:39,555
The housekeeper stopped by.

259
00:23:45,065 --> 00:23:46,065
What did she say?

260
00:23:46,295 --> 00:23:48,065
Why can't you cut people some slack?

261
00:23:48,595 --> 00:23:51,305
You fired the last one
just for not answering her phone promptly.

262
00:23:51,365 --> 00:23:53,005
She deserved it.

263
00:23:53,365 --> 00:23:55,275
Reusing disposable gloves
is a fireable offense?

264
00:23:55,905 --> 00:23:57,175
You think that was the only thing?

265
00:23:57,875 --> 00:24:01,145
She barely rinsed the cutting board
and never wiped the windowsills.

266
00:24:01,545 --> 00:24:03,315
The windowsills are spotless.

267
00:24:04,045 --> 00:24:05,045
Yong Joong.

268
00:24:05,345 --> 00:24:06,845
Are you taking the housekeeper's side
over mine?

269
00:24:07,315 --> 00:24:08,915
I'm not taking sides.
It's just a fact that...

270
00:24:09,955 --> 00:24:12,255
If you keep this up,
what if someone posts about it online?

271
00:24:12,555 --> 00:24:14,125
You'll get slammed
for being on a power trip.

272
00:24:14,855 --> 00:24:16,195
Then I'll sue them for defamation.

273
00:24:22,735 --> 00:24:23,865
You're going to fight them on it?

274
00:24:24,165 --> 00:24:26,905
That's not the way to handle it.
Nobody's perfect, you know?

275
00:24:27,035 --> 00:24:28,935
I expect to get what I pay for.
It's not like she works for free.

276
00:24:30,475 --> 00:24:32,005
Just stay out of household matters.

277
00:24:32,545 --> 00:24:33,615
You think I want to be involved?

278
00:24:34,145 --> 00:24:36,245
She came here to complain,
but you were at your get-together,

279
00:24:36,515 --> 00:24:37,915
so who else was going to deal with her?

280
00:24:37,985 --> 00:24:39,685
I had to sit here and take it all.

281
00:24:40,915 --> 00:24:41,915
The nerve of her.

282
00:24:43,185 --> 00:24:44,825
You need to treat people better.

283
00:24:44,825 --> 00:24:46,485
Why not start with me?

284
00:24:48,295 --> 00:24:49,325
When have I ever treated you poorly?

285
00:24:50,125 --> 00:24:51,495
The wife of Hyunsong Pharma's CEO...

286
00:24:51,495 --> 00:24:53,495
replaces people
until she finds the right one.

287
00:24:54,795 --> 00:24:56,465
All right, that's enough.

288
00:24:57,065 --> 00:24:58,365
You started this,
and now you want to stop?

289
00:25:00,035 --> 00:25:03,275
You shouldn't have brought it up,
or you should've put her in her place.

290
00:25:17,685 --> 00:25:20,225
Why should we have to get upset
over the housekeeper?

291
00:25:23,965 --> 00:25:24,965
This is so irritating.

292
00:25:26,365 --> 00:25:28,235
Clothes fill every single room.

293
00:25:29,395 --> 00:25:30,665
Stop buying so much stuff.

294
00:25:31,065 --> 00:25:33,705
- They're taking up all the space.
- I buy them with my own credit card.

295
00:25:33,775 --> 00:25:34,935
I don't care whose card it is.

296
00:25:35,235 --> 00:25:37,875
There's no room to walk
with your clothes, bags, and shoes.

297
00:25:37,875 --> 00:25:38,945
I'm an actress.

298
00:25:38,975 --> 00:25:40,645
But you wear sponsored outfits to events,
don't you?

299
00:25:41,045 --> 00:25:42,915
There are dozens of outfits
hanging in there with the tags still on.

300
00:25:43,885 --> 00:25:45,485
Have you been going through my things?

301
00:25:45,485 --> 00:25:46,645
This can't go on.

302
00:25:47,115 --> 00:25:49,015
If you want to buy more,
you have to get rid of some first.

303
00:25:52,585 --> 00:25:55,195
Then let's move into a house,
or build a 670m² one.

304
00:25:55,795 --> 00:25:57,825
Or if the apartment upstairs or downstairs
goes on the market, we can buy it.

305
00:25:58,225 --> 00:25:59,965
I already checked.
The one upstairs is just a rental.

306
00:26:00,265 --> 00:26:02,365
You can't be so reckless with money.

307
00:26:02,435 --> 00:26:04,505
People with money should spend it.
It helps the economy.

308
00:26:04,565 --> 00:26:07,175
If you want to spend money,
why don't you donate it to the needy?

309
00:26:07,375 --> 00:26:08,805
You already donate.

310
00:26:11,405 --> 00:26:12,575
Are you taking this out on me?

311
00:26:12,745 --> 00:26:15,275
You fire someone for being disrespectful.
You fire them if the food is too salty...

312
00:26:15,675 --> 00:26:17,345
If it's too salty, just ask them
to use less salt next time.

313
00:26:17,885 --> 00:26:18,885
It's one thing after another.

314
00:26:18,885 --> 00:26:20,915
Now you're ruining their livelihood
over some gloves.

315
00:26:21,385 --> 00:26:23,985
It's driving me crazy,
having new staff in here every other day.

316
00:26:24,125 --> 00:26:26,455
It doesn't feel like home,
and I can never relax.

317
00:26:27,325 --> 00:26:28,355
What do you mean, "every few days?"

318
00:26:28,355 --> 00:26:30,395
Why are you so obsessed with clothes?

319
00:26:30,895 --> 00:26:32,665
Don't you know the difference
between elegance and excess?

320
00:26:33,465 --> 00:26:34,495
What does that even mean?

321
00:26:35,365 --> 00:26:36,695
Fine, I'll get out of your hair.

322
00:26:42,035 --> 00:26:43,035
Darn it.

323
00:27:20,845 --> 00:27:21,845
Momo.

324
00:27:30,585 --> 00:27:35,595
(Paternity Test)

325
00:27:35,655 --> 00:27:39,965
(Paternity DNA Test)

326
00:27:43,435 --> 00:27:45,005
(Sekyul DNA Test Center,
Helixnova Gene Analysis Center)

327
00:27:45,065 --> 00:27:46,665
(Unigen Prism Center)

328
00:27:46,735 --> 00:27:48,935
(Nexergene Bio Center)

329
00:27:49,005 --> 00:27:51,675
(Paternity DNA test,
real-time and confidential)

330
00:28:27,545 --> 00:28:29,515
(Domestic, International Standard,
International Express, EMS)

331
00:28:38,255 --> 00:28:41,595
I thought I would get pregnant right away.

332
00:28:42,755 --> 00:28:45,065
But the doctors say there's nothing wrong.

333
00:28:45,365 --> 00:28:47,595
Just try to relax and be patient.

334
00:28:49,495 --> 00:28:52,735
Shopping is the easiest way
to feel better, you know?

335
00:28:53,105 --> 00:28:54,105
Mr. Ha...

336
00:28:55,675 --> 00:28:58,545
You, of all people,
should understand, right?

337
00:29:00,405 --> 00:29:01,415
But still,

338
00:29:02,275 --> 00:29:03,675
there's a limit.

339
00:29:04,285 --> 00:29:06,385
I was floored
when I stopped by the other day.

340
00:29:06,985 --> 00:29:08,885
Every room is just stuffed with clothes.

341
00:29:09,285 --> 00:29:11,355
I just haven't been myself lately.

342
00:29:13,125 --> 00:29:15,325
This is my way of coping.

343
00:29:15,625 --> 00:29:18,965
It's better than taking antidepressants
or seeing a shrink, isn't it?

344
00:29:19,095 --> 00:29:20,495
This too shall pass.

345
00:29:21,865 --> 00:29:24,305
It's not about it passing.

346
00:29:24,435 --> 00:29:26,535
I need to get pregnant.

347
00:29:26,665 --> 00:29:29,305
You're both perfectly healthy.
It'll happen.

348
00:29:30,205 --> 00:29:32,245
They say kids are a gift from the sky.

349
00:29:32,505 --> 00:29:33,705
Who says that?

350
00:29:33,975 --> 00:29:36,775
- Where is that written?
- Fine, don't believe it then.

351
00:29:39,515 --> 00:29:41,755
You can't just pack your bags
and storm out of the house.

352
00:29:43,555 --> 00:29:45,385
He hurt my pride. What else could I do?

353
00:29:45,385 --> 00:29:47,055
You think you can live on pride alone?

354
00:29:49,055 --> 00:29:50,255
Look...

355
00:29:50,625 --> 00:29:52,225
I'm Momo.

356
00:29:52,225 --> 00:29:54,565
He sent two texts, and that was it.

357
00:29:55,035 --> 00:29:57,835
Is this really what I got married for?

358
00:30:01,005 --> 00:30:04,205
I'm not going back until he gives me
a proper apology.

359
00:30:04,645 --> 00:30:06,505
He wasn't wrong, though.

360
00:30:07,005 --> 00:30:09,075
Don't take his side just
because he's your brother.

361
00:30:09,345 --> 00:30:11,815
A couple's business is their own.

362
00:30:13,045 --> 00:30:14,185
All right.

363
00:30:17,585 --> 00:30:20,655
Have you heard anything about Geum Ba Ra?

364
00:30:26,465 --> 00:30:27,465
Have you?

365
00:30:28,895 --> 00:30:31,835
I don't know. It's not certain.
They probably just imagined it.

366
00:30:33,065 --> 00:30:35,805
What was it? Come on, tell me.

367
00:30:38,345 --> 00:30:39,545
Oh, boy.

368
00:31:37,905 --> 00:31:38,905
Momo.

369
00:31:42,005 --> 00:31:43,105
Momo.

370
00:31:44,845 --> 00:31:45,845
Hey.

371
00:31:53,615 --> 00:31:56,315
I'm worried she's trembling somewhere.

372
00:31:57,455 --> 00:31:59,725
If they really saw her at Meeting Plaza,

373
00:32:01,955 --> 00:32:03,655
then she must be with someone.

374
00:32:12,365 --> 00:32:14,035
Did you really like Ba Ra?

375
00:32:18,475 --> 00:32:20,675
It was more than just
a simple crush on a girl.

376
00:32:22,915 --> 00:32:23,945
I was just drawn to her.

377
00:32:25,885 --> 00:32:26,885
Just me.

378
00:32:32,385 --> 00:32:33,885
(James)

379
00:32:37,255 --> 00:32:39,365
- Hey, James.
- You changed the door code again?

380
00:32:39,825 --> 00:32:41,265
Yes, it's 2-3-5-3, star.

381
00:32:47,235 --> 00:32:50,005
She changed it so I wouldn't
waltz in anymore.

382
00:33:28,315 --> 00:33:29,475
Remember that rainy day?

383
00:33:30,075 --> 00:33:33,415
The jajangmyeon Ba Ra made for us
was so good.

384
00:33:34,615 --> 00:33:36,015
She makes great gimbap, too.

385
00:33:38,155 --> 00:33:39,555
Do you think Ba Ra...

386
00:33:41,025 --> 00:33:42,625
ever thinks about us?

387
00:33:45,265 --> 00:33:46,325
She probably doesn't think of me.

388
00:33:46,925 --> 00:33:47,935
You?

389
00:33:48,965 --> 00:33:50,195
She could.

390
00:33:52,365 --> 00:33:54,205
She didn't want you to see her
as a little sister.

391
00:33:56,075 --> 00:33:58,075
She wanted you to see her as a woman.

392
00:34:04,015 --> 00:34:05,215
You couldn't tell?

393
00:34:06,045 --> 00:34:07,045
Seriously?

394
00:34:08,615 --> 00:34:10,385
You kept treating her like a kid,

395
00:34:10,785 --> 00:34:12,255
so she couldn't tell you how she felt.

396
00:34:13,385 --> 00:34:15,155
You know how proud she is.

397
00:34:16,655 --> 00:34:18,425
She said her pride is all she ever had.

398
00:34:19,565 --> 00:34:20,965
She really told you that?

399
00:34:28,375 --> 00:34:29,975
That's why...

400
00:34:31,005 --> 00:34:32,245
you two spent the night together.

401
00:34:32,545 --> 00:34:33,545
When?

402
00:34:34,815 --> 00:34:36,745
- Then why are you just telling me now?
- And what if I had?

403
00:34:38,345 --> 00:34:40,115
You were about to get married.

404
00:34:40,545 --> 00:34:43,685
And when I asked if you'd call yours off
if I called off mine,

405
00:34:44,955 --> 00:34:46,155
you couldn't answer.

406
00:34:50,225 --> 00:34:52,665
- Do you feel differently now?
- I don't know.

407
00:34:53,395 --> 00:34:54,835
I try not to think about it.

408
00:34:55,365 --> 00:34:56,965
You need to really look at your feelings.

409
00:34:57,465 --> 00:34:59,135
See if she's still just
little Ba Ra to you.

410
00:35:02,505 --> 00:35:04,775
But if you slept with her,
how can she be a kid?

411
00:35:08,215 --> 00:35:09,245
Exactly.

412
00:35:11,915 --> 00:35:13,685
I told her I needed some time.

413
00:35:15,815 --> 00:35:18,555
I know this is kind of personal,

414
00:35:18,955 --> 00:35:20,995
but how is it living with Momo?

415
00:35:23,325 --> 00:35:25,465
I just feel pathetic.

416
00:35:26,295 --> 00:35:28,165
Your feelings for someone
aren't supposed to change.

417
00:35:29,335 --> 00:35:30,695
If they didn't, you'd be a robot.

418
00:35:31,605 --> 00:35:35,075
To be honest,
Momo isn't the person I imagined.

419
00:35:40,775 --> 00:35:42,815
And Ba Ra isn't
who I thought she was either.

420
00:35:49,215 --> 00:35:51,025
So what are you going to do?

421
00:35:51,985 --> 00:35:53,355
What can I do?

422
00:35:54,225 --> 00:35:55,825
There's no way to find Ba Ra.

423
00:35:56,695 --> 00:35:58,465
I'm married. I have to be responsible.

424
00:35:58,595 --> 00:36:00,225
You should have realized it sooner.

425
00:36:00,895 --> 00:36:01,935
Seriously?

426
00:36:07,005 --> 00:36:09,635
I'm not making excuses,
but I thought Ba Ra...

427
00:36:09,905 --> 00:36:11,605
had feelings for you.

428
00:36:11,945 --> 00:36:13,805
It was just gratitude for my position,

429
00:36:14,745 --> 00:36:16,115
nothing more, nothing less.

430
00:36:16,875 --> 00:36:18,585
She was good to me when we were together.

431
00:36:19,315 --> 00:36:20,945
She'd put so much care
into cooking for me.

432
00:36:21,455 --> 00:36:23,155
She'd even send food
to the operating room.

433
00:36:24,755 --> 00:36:26,955
Things like that just
keep popping into my head.

434
00:36:29,455 --> 00:36:30,455
I can't stop thinking about them.

435
00:36:39,465 --> 00:36:40,835
The thing I don't get is,

436
00:36:41,875 --> 00:36:44,105
am I just unable to forget that one night,

437
00:36:46,805 --> 00:36:49,215
or have I actually fallen
for her as a woman?

438
00:36:52,215 --> 00:36:53,345
It's probably a bit of both.

439
00:36:55,185 --> 00:36:58,025
They say life never goes the way you plan.

440
00:36:58,855 --> 00:37:00,425
For all we know, Ba Ra...

441
00:37:01,395 --> 00:37:03,925
might not care about either of us anymore.

442
00:37:05,895 --> 00:37:07,125
And here we are, still doing this.

443
00:37:09,595 --> 00:37:10,965
We hear rain and run out,

444
00:37:11,805 --> 00:37:13,465
hoping she's there.

445
00:37:16,675 --> 00:37:18,375
There is no way she hasn't forgotten.

446
00:37:19,945 --> 00:37:22,215
Ba Ra was even hospitalized.

447
00:37:31,485 --> 00:37:34,895
She wasn't in any condition to fly,
so I had her stay at my place.

448
00:37:35,995 --> 00:37:40,225
If you hadn't shown up that day,
Ba Ra would've left for Boston.

449
00:37:40,965 --> 00:37:42,665
And I would've had to just let her go.

450
00:37:46,405 --> 00:37:47,805
I asked her what she liked
so much about you.

451
00:37:49,075 --> 00:37:51,075
She said her whole life was just for you.

452
00:37:55,145 --> 00:37:58,085
At first, when she was young,

453
00:37:58,685 --> 00:38:01,315
her only goal was to be successful
so she could see you again.

454
00:38:01,885 --> 00:38:03,285
But then it turned into something more.

455
00:38:05,485 --> 00:38:06,855
Of course she would.

456
00:38:10,825 --> 00:38:12,665
But you only had eyes for Momo.

457
00:38:14,395 --> 00:38:16,295
It must have been so hard for her,
just watching.

458
00:38:22,305 --> 00:38:25,275
She figured if you knew how she felt,
you'd decide to marry her.

459
00:38:26,475 --> 00:38:27,645
She said that, out of a sense of duty,

460
00:38:28,845 --> 00:38:30,975
forcing your feelings
would be meaningless.

461
00:38:46,565 --> 00:38:48,865
When did you get here?
You should've just gone home.

462
00:38:49,095 --> 00:38:50,835
I already dropped Momo off there.

463
00:38:51,165 --> 00:38:52,535
This is my home too.

464
00:38:58,475 --> 00:39:00,875
Unless you're planning on leaving her,
go easy on her.

465
00:39:01,415 --> 00:39:03,375
After all, you two got married
because you were in love.

466
00:39:04,045 --> 00:39:07,385
She lost the baby, and she's anxious
about having trouble conceiving.

467
00:39:08,455 --> 00:39:09,555
Has Ba Ra...

468
00:39:11,155 --> 00:39:12,885
ever said anything to you about me?

469
00:39:13,855 --> 00:39:15,595
No. She would not have.

470
00:39:15,955 --> 00:39:18,665
- Why?
- Is there really no way to find her?

471
00:39:19,225 --> 00:39:22,435
She obviously left for a personal reason.
What good would finding her do?

472
00:39:22,595 --> 00:39:24,465
The best way to help her
is to leave her be.

473
00:39:28,475 --> 00:39:29,835
All of us...

474
00:39:30,605 --> 00:39:32,375
ever really knew Ba Ra at all.

475
00:39:33,245 --> 00:39:36,415
You can never truly know
what's in someone's heart.

476
00:39:36,975 --> 00:39:38,815
Sometimes I don't even know my own mind.

477
00:39:43,185 --> 00:39:46,525
There's no point in dwelling on it.
Just focus on Momo.

478
00:39:55,895 --> 00:39:57,135
I'll make you some soup.

479
00:40:26,065 --> 00:40:30,565
You treat Momo better than me.
I was jealous and upset.

480
00:40:31,405 --> 00:40:33,065
She told me exactly how she felt,

481
00:40:34,065 --> 00:40:35,135
and I had no idea.

482
00:40:36,675 --> 00:40:38,005
Where are you, Geum Ba Ra?

483
00:40:55,795 --> 00:40:57,855
(Test Results)

484
00:41:02,995 --> 00:41:05,835
(DNA match test results:
99.9 percent match)

485
00:41:09,635 --> 00:41:12,775
(Paternity is established
between Kim Young Jun and Geum Ba Ra)

486
00:41:24,115 --> 00:41:26,655
(Paternity is established
between Kim Young Jun and Geum Ba Ra)

487
00:42:25,515 --> 00:42:28,155
Could Artist Kim Young Jun really be...

488
00:42:29,085 --> 00:42:30,385
my dad?

489
00:42:30,455 --> 00:42:32,425
(Could Artist Kim Young Jun
really be my father?)

490
00:44:01,515 --> 00:44:03,075
You're gorgeous!

491
00:44:03,615 --> 00:44:05,485
- Can you look over here, please?
- Thank you.

492
00:44:05,545 --> 00:44:06,845
Momo, could I get a picture with you, too?

493
00:44:06,915 --> 00:44:08,785
- Sure.
- Thank you.

494
00:44:09,815 --> 00:44:12,555
- Okay, ready?
- One, two, three.

495
00:44:16,195 --> 00:44:17,295
You're so, so pretty.

496
00:44:17,295 --> 00:44:19,925
- Thank you so much.
- Thank you.

497
00:44:20,495 --> 00:44:22,135
- You're even prettier in person.
- Thank you.

498
00:44:22,135 --> 00:44:25,135
- Can I get one too?
- I'm sorry, but we have to get going now.

499
00:44:25,205 --> 00:44:26,605
Get home safe.

500
00:44:27,505 --> 00:44:28,835
Take care!

501
00:44:29,275 --> 00:44:30,305
I know, right?

502
00:44:37,745 --> 00:44:40,845
Of all the photos taken of me in Korea,
this is my favorite.

503
00:44:49,595 --> 00:44:52,565
(Artist Kim Young Jun)

504
00:44:59,135 --> 00:45:01,675
(Artist Kim Young Jun)

505
00:45:48,715 --> 00:45:49,755
What's this?

506
00:46:00,395 --> 00:46:02,095
I went to the hospital today,

507
00:46:02,095 --> 00:46:04,035
and the doctor suggested
a fertility clinic,

508
00:46:04,035 --> 00:46:05,235
even if nothing's technically wrong.

509
00:46:06,405 --> 00:46:07,965
You can make time on Friday, can't you?

510
00:46:09,705 --> 00:46:11,035
It won't take long.

511
00:46:11,905 --> 00:46:13,705
No. Why would we do that?

512
00:46:14,775 --> 00:46:15,945
I'm anxious, okay?

513
00:46:16,215 --> 00:46:17,345
You have nothing to be anxious about.

514
00:46:18,045 --> 00:46:19,585
You want a baby too, don't you?

515
00:46:20,215 --> 00:46:21,385
Let's just let nature take its course.

516
00:46:22,055 --> 00:46:24,385
It's not hard.
All we have to do is show up.

517
00:46:27,285 --> 00:46:29,425
If you want to be a father,
then cooperate.

518
00:46:32,525 --> 00:46:34,825
- Watch your tone.
- I'm the one who'd bear your child.

519
00:46:35,465 --> 00:46:37,235
I'm the one who has to go through it all
if we start treatments.

520
00:46:37,295 --> 00:46:38,505
Exactly. So who's asking you to do it?

521
00:46:38,935 --> 00:46:40,665
Have we been trying for five years?
Or ten?

522
00:46:41,005 --> 00:46:43,875
It's not like we have parents pushing us,
so why are you so obsessed with this?

523
00:46:44,705 --> 00:46:45,705
Obsessed?

524
00:46:46,045 --> 00:46:47,505
It's about our child, not an obsession.

525
00:46:47,705 --> 00:46:49,175
The child isn't even born yet.

526
00:46:49,245 --> 00:46:51,045
And you're too busy
with your games to care.

527
00:46:51,045 --> 00:46:52,115
You think I'm just playing around?

528
00:46:52,245 --> 00:46:55,285
I need something too!
What's so hard about one doctor's visit?

529
00:46:56,855 --> 00:46:58,385
Just do this for me once.

530
00:46:58,455 --> 00:47:01,285
I've done everything you've ever wanted.
I buy you everything you ask for.

531
00:47:02,025 --> 00:47:03,255
It's easy for you
to just throw money at things.

532
00:47:04,295 --> 00:47:05,325
Money and time.

533
00:47:05,625 --> 00:47:07,865
I shop with you for hours when you want.

534
00:47:07,865 --> 00:47:09,635
- What more do you want from me?
- And me?

535
00:47:10,235 --> 00:47:11,235
What have you done?

536
00:47:13,635 --> 00:47:15,575
- I'm Momo.
- So what...

537
00:47:19,245 --> 00:47:20,245
if you're Momo?

538
00:47:20,905 --> 00:47:22,575
You want a medal
for doing the bare minimum?

539
00:47:22,945 --> 00:47:24,875
- A medal?
- What else would you call it?

540
00:47:25,615 --> 00:47:27,945
I'm saying I did my best as your husband.

541
00:47:28,245 --> 00:47:30,655
So as your wife,
I'm offering to have your baby.

542
00:47:32,025 --> 00:47:34,955
Maybe we can think about it in a few years
if it doesn't happen.

543
00:47:38,295 --> 00:47:40,225
At least Shin Ju Shin
had some paternal instinct.

544
00:47:42,665 --> 00:47:46,465
Is it wrong to want a baby
so we can finally be a happy family?

545
00:47:46,535 --> 00:47:48,475
Then you should've stayed with Ju Shin
and been happy.

546
00:47:49,875 --> 00:47:51,375
Don't you dare compare me to him!

547
00:47:54,805 --> 00:47:55,845
You're so two-faced.

548
00:47:58,945 --> 00:48:00,915
Then go find your precious, pregnant Ba Ra
and live together.

549
00:48:01,515 --> 00:48:02,985
I heard James's employee saw her.

550
00:48:03,755 --> 00:48:04,755
Let's just end it!

551
00:48:06,085 --> 00:48:07,985
Geum Ba Ra tried to have it all
and ended up with nothing.

552
00:48:08,055 --> 00:48:10,695
I bet she shacked up with some nobody
and is having his kid somewhere.

553
00:48:10,825 --> 00:48:13,465
Too embarrassed to show her face,
just hiding away.

554
00:48:14,895 --> 00:48:15,895
Darn it.

555
00:48:32,815 --> 00:48:34,345
If you're not coming back,
then pack your bags.

556
00:48:35,485 --> 00:48:38,255
I said it's over. I'll sign the papers.

557
00:48:41,955 --> 00:48:43,025
Are you sure you won't regret this?

558
00:48:48,665 --> 00:48:49,665
You bastard.

559
00:49:32,775 --> 00:49:34,145
It could just be false labor.

560
00:49:34,745 --> 00:49:36,415
Your due date isn't for another ten days.

561
00:49:36,975 --> 00:49:38,015
Thank you.

562
00:49:39,015 --> 00:49:40,045
Especially on a Sunday.

563
00:49:40,445 --> 00:49:42,455
It wouldn't matter if it were
the middle of the night.

564
00:49:43,115 --> 00:49:44,115
Is your doctor coming in?

565
00:49:45,185 --> 00:49:46,455
Yes.

566
00:49:46,455 --> 00:49:48,825
Well, the baby's dropped,
so it could be time.

567
00:49:51,255 --> 00:49:53,795
(Solpyeong Women's Clinic)

568
00:49:56,095 --> 00:49:59,465
Okay, take a big deep breath in,
and exhale.

569
00:49:59,935 --> 00:50:03,135
Okay, bear down and give a big push.
Take a breath and push!

570
00:50:04,305 --> 00:50:07,175
Yes, good. Keep pushing.

571
00:50:07,805 --> 00:50:08,815
Yes, just like that.

572
00:50:12,145 --> 00:50:14,445
It's impossible without
a formal police investigation.

573
00:50:14,845 --> 00:50:16,655
Personal privacy laws are
so much stricter these days.

574
00:50:16,915 --> 00:50:19,385
Even my police contacts are lying low.

575
00:50:19,385 --> 00:50:20,655
Well, I appreciate the effort.

576
00:50:21,225 --> 00:50:22,225
I'm sorry.

577
00:50:22,795 --> 00:50:23,795
It is what it is.

578
00:50:26,525 --> 00:50:27,525
My baby...

579
00:50:29,895 --> 00:50:31,195
You're not alone.

580
00:50:32,535 --> 00:50:36,135
Mommy's here, and so is your grandfather.

581
00:50:38,475 --> 00:50:39,645
You're doing great.

582
00:50:39,905 --> 00:50:41,045
Okay, one more.

583
00:50:41,675 --> 00:50:42,675
Last one.

584
00:50:43,475 --> 00:50:44,475
A little more.

585
00:50:47,445 --> 00:50:48,445
Just a little bit more.

586
00:50:49,055 --> 00:50:50,855
Okay, you're almost there!

587
00:50:54,125 --> 00:50:55,425
There we go.

588
00:50:57,225 --> 00:50:58,895
You did great, Mom.

589
00:51:23,585 --> 00:51:25,385
I want to hold my baby.

590
00:51:28,225 --> 00:51:30,995
Here you go.

591
00:52:12,305 --> 00:52:15,305
The father must be very handsome.
He's absolutely gorgeous.

592
00:52:21,175 --> 00:52:22,545
Could you take...

593
00:52:23,415 --> 00:52:25,115
a picture for us?

594
00:52:31,055 --> 00:52:32,755
Stop drinking that ice water.

595
00:52:33,885 --> 00:52:34,885
I'm fine.

596
00:52:38,025 --> 00:52:39,025
So, what are you going to do?

597
00:52:39,365 --> 00:52:42,065
She stormed out like that.
She's probably filing for divorce.

598
00:52:42,195 --> 00:52:44,665
What good will a divorce do her?
It's her own loss.

599
00:52:44,965 --> 00:52:46,065
First a broken engagement, now a divorce.

600
00:52:46,405 --> 00:52:48,005
An actress lives and dies
by her public image.

601
00:52:54,245 --> 00:52:55,915
I made a mistake I can't take back.

602
00:52:56,815 --> 00:52:57,945
You hit Momo?

603
00:52:58,645 --> 00:52:59,645
To Ba Ra.

604
00:53:00,185 --> 00:53:01,415
What did you do to her?

605
00:53:02,655 --> 00:53:03,685
I have to find Ba Ra.

606
00:53:04,115 --> 00:53:06,125
How are you going to find someone
who's determined to stay hidden?

607
00:53:07,225 --> 00:53:08,525
Momo's probably right.

608
00:53:09,195 --> 00:53:11,225
She got lonely and ended up
with some loser.

609
00:53:12,225 --> 00:53:13,265
Don't you know Ba Ra?

610
00:53:13,895 --> 00:53:15,565
She even pushed Ju Shin away and left.

611
00:53:15,935 --> 00:53:17,935
- What could possibly...
- It might be my baby.

612
00:53:20,505 --> 00:53:22,435
But if she's six or seven months along,

613
00:53:24,335 --> 00:53:25,345
the timeline doesn't add up.

614
00:53:27,405 --> 00:53:28,405
Exactly.

615
00:53:29,975 --> 00:53:31,345
So, you're saying, you and Reporter Geum?

616
00:53:36,885 --> 00:53:39,125
Oh my gosh.

617
00:53:45,895 --> 00:53:47,925
- I'm heading in.
- Okay.

618
00:53:48,765 --> 00:53:50,835
- Could you look after Grandmother?
- Don't worry.

619
00:53:51,565 --> 00:53:54,835
When she saw the baby's picture,
she said he was very handsome.

620
00:54:10,985 --> 00:54:13,525
(Test Results)

621
00:54:18,095 --> 00:54:21,325
(Paternity is established
between Kim Young Jun and Geum Ba Ra)

622
00:54:22,135 --> 00:54:24,495
(Match)

623
00:54:48,285 --> 00:54:49,295
Yes, sir.

624
00:54:49,995 --> 00:54:52,565
When Reporter Geum Ba Ra was
at Meeting Plaza, was she at full term,

625
00:54:52,565 --> 00:54:53,895
or six or seven months pregnant?

626
00:54:54,125 --> 00:54:57,435
- Try to remember exactly.
- She wasn't full-term.

627
00:54:57,635 --> 00:54:58,695
Didn't you see her from far away?

628
00:54:58,835 --> 00:55:00,035
About ten meters away.

629
00:55:00,235 --> 00:55:02,575
I could tell she was pregnant right away,
so I was surprised,

630
00:55:02,575 --> 00:55:04,435
so I stared for a few seconds.

631
00:55:04,705 --> 00:55:05,905
You're sure it was six or seven months?

632
00:55:06,375 --> 00:55:09,215
Yes. Or maybe even five months?

633
00:55:10,415 --> 00:55:12,515
- All right.
- Yes, sir.

634
00:55:18,585 --> 00:55:20,755
Is this a love story
or some crazy soap opera?

635
00:55:22,625 --> 00:55:23,825
It's not a total soap opera.

636
00:55:26,895 --> 00:55:28,865
Then who on earth did she meet?

637
00:55:31,795 --> 00:55:33,265
She has the worst luck.

638
00:55:41,745 --> 00:55:42,815
So what are you going to do?

639
00:55:45,945 --> 00:55:47,115
Should I get the papers ready?

640
00:55:48,485 --> 00:55:49,515
How much are you offering?

641
00:55:52,085 --> 00:55:53,185
For alimony.

642
00:55:53,185 --> 00:55:55,185
Shouldn't I be the one getting paid?

643
00:55:55,695 --> 00:55:57,025
Since I'm the one being divorced here.

644
00:55:59,865 --> 00:56:01,865
- How much do you want?
- Half.

645
00:56:04,695 --> 00:56:05,905
Are you serious?

646
00:56:07,065 --> 00:56:08,065
Dead serious.

647
00:56:20,015 --> 00:56:21,445
I don't resent you.

648
00:56:22,415 --> 00:56:23,555
I'm grateful.

649
00:56:24,785 --> 00:56:27,855
If it weren't for you, I would've spent
my whole life as an orphan.

650
00:56:29,555 --> 00:56:31,655
Because of you, I have my baby,

651
00:56:32,265 --> 00:56:34,295
and I even found my birth father.

652
00:56:35,965 --> 00:56:36,965
Thank you.

653
00:56:38,165 --> 00:56:39,465
Thank you so much.

654
00:57:23,445 --> 00:57:24,775
I'm having the birthday soup...

655
00:57:25,985 --> 00:57:27,185
that my father made...

656
00:57:50,235 --> 00:57:52,175
Maybe I should've just
married the director.

657
00:57:52,975 --> 00:57:56,275
He seemed cold,
but he had a warm side to him.

658
00:58:11,055 --> 00:58:12,495
(Momo. Born: February 14, 2002.
Occupation: Actress)

659
00:58:15,295 --> 00:58:19,165
(Momo: No Comment on Separation Rumors)

660
00:58:19,235 --> 00:58:24,635
(Is Momo Getting Divorced?
Confirmed Living in Her Old Villa)

661
00:58:24,705 --> 00:58:27,045
(Momo Remains Silent on Separation...
Divorce Rumors Resurface)

662
00:58:27,045 --> 00:58:28,505
(Is Momo Getting Divorced?
Confirmed Living in Her Old Villa)

663
00:58:28,575 --> 00:58:30,015
(Momo Remains Silent on Separation...
Divorce Rumors Resurface)

664
00:58:56,305 --> 00:58:58,005
This is so pathetic.

665
00:58:58,005 --> 00:58:59,175
I look so pathetic.

666
00:59:03,015 --> 00:59:04,375
Seriously.

667
00:59:10,685 --> 00:59:11,915
Should I just admit I was wrong?

668
00:59:12,885 --> 00:59:14,985
Then that softy Ha Yong Joong
would just let it all go.

669
00:59:29,175 --> 00:59:31,875
Internal medicine specialists and interns,

670
00:59:31,935 --> 00:59:34,705
please report to the third floor
immediately.

671
00:59:37,715 --> 00:59:39,515
(International Call)

672
00:59:45,355 --> 00:59:46,785
(International Call)

673
00:59:52,625 --> 00:59:55,465
- Hello?
- Reporter Geum, I see you called.

674
00:59:56,865 --> 00:59:57,865
I did.

675
00:59:58,465 --> 01:00:00,035
Is everything okay at the house?

676
01:00:05,975 --> 01:00:06,975
Yes, it's nothing.

677
01:00:07,545 --> 01:00:10,845
A shelf on the bookcase fell off.

678
01:00:16,585 --> 01:00:17,785
When are you coming back?

679
01:00:18,985 --> 01:00:20,185
How's the patient doing?

680
01:00:21,125 --> 01:00:24,455
The doctor says
he won't last another three months.

681
01:00:26,025 --> 01:00:27,025
I'm the daughter...

682
01:00:27,095 --> 01:00:28,725
(I'm the daughter...)

683
01:00:28,825 --> 01:00:30,295
you've been...

684
01:00:30,365 --> 01:00:33,065
(I'm the daughter you've been...)

685
01:00:33,135 --> 01:00:34,365
searching for.

686
01:00:42,915 --> 01:00:43,915
Hello?

687
01:00:47,385 --> 01:00:48,515
Yes, Mr. Kim.

688
01:00:48,915 --> 01:00:50,015
Do you have a cold?

689
01:00:52,785 --> 01:00:53,855
Yes, a little...

690
01:00:59,025 --> 01:01:00,295
Thanks anyway.

691
01:01:00,995 --> 01:01:02,795
Do you need anything?
I can grab it on my way.

692
01:01:03,435 --> 01:01:04,435
No, I'm good.

693
01:01:08,635 --> 01:01:09,875
Wait. For a baby...

694
01:01:11,605 --> 01:01:12,605
Baby?

695
01:01:13,705 --> 01:01:14,705
Never mind.

696
01:01:16,445 --> 01:01:18,575
A friend of mine just had a baby,

697
01:01:20,945 --> 01:01:22,515
so I was wondering, maybe a baby toy?

698
01:01:23,715 --> 01:01:25,855
Got it. A baby toy.

699
01:01:26,625 --> 01:01:28,055
I'll let you go then, Mr. Kim.

700
01:01:28,685 --> 01:01:30,695
Okay, yes. It's a bit noisy here.

701
01:01:32,195 --> 01:01:33,195
Okay.

702
01:01:42,835 --> 01:01:44,275
Father.

703
01:01:49,575 --> 01:01:50,745
Dad.

704
01:02:53,175 --> 01:02:54,375
Don't bite your nails.

705
01:02:56,315 --> 01:02:57,745
Those are my sister's nails.

706
01:02:57,845 --> 01:02:59,915
(Those are my sister's nails)

707
01:03:05,615 --> 01:03:06,625
What happened?

708
01:03:08,425 --> 01:03:09,425
Say something.

709
01:03:10,955 --> 01:03:11,955
Say something.

710
01:03:33,845 --> 01:03:35,615
I went down to the countryside
to get some rest.

711
01:04:17,025 --> 01:04:18,055
(Brother-in-law)

712
01:04:37,115 --> 01:04:38,615
Honey, I was wrong.

713
01:04:42,915 --> 01:04:44,055
Please forgive me.

714
01:04:48,785 --> 01:04:51,025
I just wanted you to baby me.

715
01:04:52,025 --> 01:04:54,895
I won't stress over having a baby anymore.
I'll leave it to fate.

716
01:04:54,965 --> 01:04:56,395
From now on, I'll live only for you.

717
01:05:01,305 --> 01:05:02,935
Can I get you something cold? A beer?

718
01:05:02,935 --> 01:05:04,005
No.

719
01:05:04,135 --> 01:05:06,075
- Champagne?
- I'm not in the mood.

720
01:05:41,945 --> 01:05:43,715
I'm a man of my word.

721
01:05:55,155 --> 01:05:56,325
I made myself clear.

722
01:05:56,755 --> 01:05:58,125
I said to pack your bags
if you weren't coming home.

723
01:06:18,245 --> 01:06:19,615
I said I'm sorry!

724
01:06:20,545 --> 01:06:22,315
You take everything too lightly.

725
01:06:22,885 --> 01:06:25,455
- You only think about yourself.
- That's not true.

726
01:06:36,995 --> 01:06:38,695
I promise I'll do better from now on.

727
01:06:39,235 --> 01:06:40,765
I'll never upset you again.

728
01:06:45,135 --> 01:06:47,105
I won't be harsh on the housekeepers.

729
01:06:47,845 --> 01:06:49,575
It's all part of
learning to live together.

730
01:06:50,245 --> 01:06:54,315
I feel like I finally understand you now.
I really do.

731
01:06:54,385 --> 01:06:55,385
The feeling's mutual.

732
01:06:57,085 --> 01:06:58,085
We're not compatible.

733
01:07:01,855 --> 01:07:02,925
There's nothing more to say.

734
01:07:04,425 --> 01:07:05,595
Honey, in life...

735
01:07:05,655 --> 01:07:07,665
Sure, couples can bicker
from time to time.

736
01:07:11,865 --> 01:07:13,335
But what did I do that was so wrong?

737
01:07:13,605 --> 01:07:15,905
Now that we're ending things,
I don't want to list every single thing.

738
01:07:16,335 --> 01:07:17,435
"Ending things?"

739
01:07:17,805 --> 01:07:19,305
I'll get the papers ready.

740
01:07:23,215 --> 01:07:24,815
How much alimony are you going to give me?

741
01:07:27,515 --> 01:07:28,785
I'll discuss it with my lawyer.

742
01:07:44,135 --> 01:07:46,465
I'm Momo.
First a broken engagement, now a divorce?

743
01:07:46,535 --> 01:07:49,335
- I'll take the fall.
- And what becomes of my life?

744
01:07:50,105 --> 01:07:53,205
You brought this on yourself.
Don't take what I say as a joke.

745
01:07:55,475 --> 01:07:56,545
Don't you love me?

746
01:07:56,975 --> 01:07:57,975
You did.

747
01:07:58,815 --> 01:07:59,945
I've thought about it.

748
01:08:01,285 --> 01:08:03,285
It was closer to fascination than love,

749
01:08:03,885 --> 01:08:06,585
but whether it's love or fascination,
it's still a feeling.

750
01:08:07,625 --> 01:08:09,255
But I'll be honest about how I feel now.

751
01:08:10,795 --> 01:08:11,855
I'm completely over you.

752
01:08:13,895 --> 01:08:14,895
That bastard.

753
01:08:15,925 --> 01:08:16,935
That bastard!

754
01:08:17,865 --> 01:08:19,135
How can you be so cruel?

755
01:08:20,065 --> 01:08:22,605
- I had my own complaints, you know.
- Like what?

756
01:08:22,835 --> 01:08:24,835
You were always thinking about Geum Ba Ra,
weren't you?

757
01:08:25,375 --> 01:08:26,375
I know.

758
01:08:28,245 --> 01:08:29,245
Right?

759
01:08:31,915 --> 01:08:33,645
I was the one who had to
put up with it all!

760
01:08:34,145 --> 01:08:35,945
I was the one who had to
put up with it all!

761
01:08:36,385 --> 01:08:39,355
In any case,
I did my best as your husband.

762
01:08:39,415 --> 01:08:41,025
You did your best acting the part.

763
01:08:41,785 --> 01:08:43,295
The point is, we're both over each other.

764
01:08:47,865 --> 01:08:50,235
Fine, I'll give you a divorce
after I have a baby.

765
01:08:51,835 --> 01:08:54,805
I'll have a baby and devote my life to it.
You can do that much, can't you?

766
01:08:55,265 --> 01:08:57,435
I'm so done with men.

767
01:09:05,475 --> 01:09:07,745
No! I won't break up with you! I can't!

768
01:09:08,485 --> 01:09:10,015
I refuse to be humiliated again.

769
01:09:10,015 --> 01:09:11,455
How pathetic would that make me look?

770
01:09:11,515 --> 01:09:13,485
My mom died, my engagement was broken,
and now a divorce?

771
01:09:14,125 --> 01:09:15,285
I might as well be dead.

772
01:09:15,755 --> 01:09:16,755
Hey!

773
01:09:39,745 --> 01:09:42,515
Hey, what's all this?
Calm down and talk it out.

774
01:09:43,755 --> 01:09:45,055
I'll give you two some space.

775
01:09:49,255 --> 01:09:50,255
Put on your coat.

776
01:09:52,625 --> 01:09:53,625
Why?

777
01:09:54,025 --> 01:09:55,065
Please talk to her.

778
01:10:00,205 --> 01:10:01,265
He wants a divorce!

779
01:10:03,405 --> 01:10:04,835
Oh, not like that.

780
01:10:07,105 --> 01:10:08,475
Hurry up and put the side dishes
in the fridge.

781
01:10:22,955 --> 01:10:24,355
Whatever happens, happens.

782
01:10:44,815 --> 01:10:47,015
(Ju Shin)

783
01:10:51,415 --> 01:10:53,325
- Hello?
- Ba Ra is in the hospital.

784
01:10:56,185 --> 01:10:58,725
- Ba Ra?
- Yes, today.

785
01:11:01,095 --> 01:11:02,825
What happened? Is she sick?

786
01:11:03,265 --> 01:11:06,065
It's nothing serious,
but we're going to run some tests.

787
01:11:59,485 --> 01:12:02,285
(Doctor Shin)

788
01:12:03,295 --> 01:12:06,325
Do you really think you can be happy,
Ha Yong Joong, after making me cry?

789
01:12:07,065 --> 01:12:09,195
I'm going to make your life
a living torment.

790
01:12:10,065 --> 01:12:11,635
I'll have ten kids
if that's what it takes.

791
01:12:12,195 --> 01:12:13,205
As many as we can have.

792
01:12:14,165 --> 01:12:16,165
- Did you get married?
- Were you seeing someone?

793
01:12:16,235 --> 01:12:17,805
Her hemoglobin is low,

794
01:12:17,805 --> 01:12:19,605
so I'm thinking of an MRI this weekend,
just in case.

795
01:12:19,675 --> 01:12:21,805
Did she say anything else?
Like how she's been?

796
01:12:21,875 --> 01:12:24,315
I'll become you and live as Geum Ba Ra.

797
01:12:24,315 --> 01:12:26,445
Living as Momo can't be that bad.

798
01:12:26,445 --> 01:12:27,515
Why do you want to become me?

799
01:12:27,585 --> 01:12:29,645
With that face and that body,

800
01:12:30,285 --> 01:12:31,955
there's no reason to cling to them.

801
01:12:31,955 --> 01:12:34,455
Think of all the tears you've shed.

802
01:12:34,525 --> 01:12:36,225
Thank you.
And don't forget what I told you.

803
01:12:36,285 --> 01:12:38,595
I'm never letting you go again,
Geum Ba Ra.

804
01:12:38,655 --> 01:12:39,925
Can you accept...

805
01:12:40,995 --> 01:12:42,295
my child too?

806
01:12:42,295 --> 01:12:43,795
It's only the first step that's hard.

807
01:12:44,095 --> 01:12:45,995
You're just asleep for a few hours,
and then you wake up.

808
01:12:45,995 --> 01:12:47,065
It's no big deal.

809
01:12:49,305 --> 01:12:51,235
- You scream, and you'll regret it!
- Dad!

810
01:12:51,235 --> 01:12:53,375
It's me, Jin Ju.

811
01:12:53,645 --> 01:12:56,345
I'm Momo now! We swapped brains!

812
01:12:56,345 --> 01:12:57,545
Don't give me that crap.

813
01:12:58,145 --> 01:12:59,275
Ma'am!

814
01:12:59,415 --> 01:13:00,585
Are you all right?

815
01:13:03,685 --> 01:13:05,685
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
